    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <details>
            <summary>What does 'S-Tier' mean in a Pokemon Unite tier list?</summary>
            <p>S-Tier represents the absolute highest ranking. Pokemon in this tier are considered exceptionally strong, meta-defining, and advantageous to pick in almost any team composition.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>How often do Pokemon Unite tier lists change?</summary>
            <p>Tier lists change frequently, typically after every major game update or balance patch. They can also shift when players discover new strategies or item combinations.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>Should I only play S-Tier and A-Tier Pokemon?</summary>
            <p>Not necessarily. While higher-tier Pokemon offer statistical advantages, player skill, comfort with a character's mechanics, and team synergy are often more important than raw tier placement.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>What factors determine a Pokemon's placement on the tier list?</summary>
            <p>Placements are determined by a combination of raw stats (damage, health), mobility, crowd control abilities, utility, and how well the character performs against other popular meta picks.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>Who creates these tier lists?</summary>
            <p>Tier lists are usually created by high-ranking competitive players, dedicated content creators, or analytical websites that aggregate win-rate data and community feedback.</p>
        </details>
    </section>
